The paper deals with verifying the correctness of concurrent data structures, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of programming languages (cs.PL), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, since the paper focuses on linearisability, which is a property of concurrent data structures, it is most likely to be classified under cs.PL or cs.DS.
